t (fewest 1s), then lexicographically smallest\n\n### Free Variable Enumeration\n\n- k = number of free variables (columns without pivots)\n- If k <= 25, enumerate all 2^k combinations (2^25 = ~33M, feasible in 5s)\n- For each combination, compute the implied pivot variable values\n- Track the best solution (minimum weight, then lex smallest)\n\n## Part 2: Counter Puzzle (GF(p))\n\n### Mathematical Model\n\n- N counters, M buttons, prime modulus p\n- Each button press increments specific counters by 1\n- State equation: A * x = b (mod p)\n  - A[i][j] = 1 if button j affects counter i, else 0\n  - x[j] = number of times button j is pressed (0 to p-1)\n  - b[i] = target value for counter i\n\n### Algorithm\n\n1. Build augmented matrix [A | b]\n2. Gaussian elimination over GF(p) using modular inverse\n3. Check consistency\n4. Identify free variables\n5. Enumerate all p^k assignments of free variables\n6. For each assignment, back-substitute to get full solution\n7. Select solution with minimum sum, then lexicographically smallest\n\n### Modular Arithmetic\n\n- Addition: (a + b) mod p\n- Subtraction: (a - b + p) mod p\n- Multiplication: (a * b) mod p\n- Division: a * modInverse(b, p) mod p\n- modInverse via Fermat's little theorem: b^(p-2) mod p (since p is prime)\n\n### Free Variable Feasibility\n\n- For p^k to be enumerable in 5s:\n  - p=2: k<=25\n  - p=3: k<=15\n  - p=5: k<=10\n  - p=97: k<=4\n- In practice, systems with 40 equations and 40 unknowns rarely have many free variables\n\n## Optimization: Lexicographic Ordering\n\nFor both puzzles, when comparing solutions:\n1. Primary: minimum cost (weight for toggle, sum for counter)\n2. Secondary: lexicographically smallest array\n\n## Error Handling\n\n- Return null if system is inconsistent\n- Handle edge cases: empty target, no buttons, all lights already correct\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n- Unit tests for GF arithmetic\n- Small toggle puzzle examples\n- Small counter puzzle examples\n- Edge cases: no solution, unique solution, multiple solutions\n- Performance test with 40x40 matrices\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
